* zzapper <david@tvis.co.uk> typed:
> How do I write a variable expansion which will remove a file extension eg 
> fred.tex -> fred
> 
> This is what I hacked:-
> 
> zip=${file//\.[[:alnum:]]*/}

Use ``${foo:r}''. ":r" remove a filename extension; its described in
zshexpn(1) /Modifiers

